  "What is the 'upper bound' rule in the context of testing zeros?": "",
  "The largest possible rational zero is always the constant term": "",
  "The upper bound is the degree of the polynomial": "",
  "No zero can exceed the leading coefficient": "",
  "If synthetic division by c > 0 produces all non-negative values, then c is an upper bound for real zeros": "",
  "The upper bound theorem states that if you perform synthetic division with a positive c and all resulting coefficients are non-negative, then no real zero is greater than c.": "",
  "What does 'systematic testing' mean when applying the Rational Root Theorem?": "",
